    Categories of Selectors :-
    I - General Selector
    a. using the tag name
    - if you want to give effect to the element then use 

    b. using the id name
    c. using the class
    d. Using grouping elements : if you want to give the same effect to the group of elements,Elements name seprated by comma.
    e. Using the Universal Selector:-
    -if you want to give effects to all the elements inthe html document then use the universal Selector
    - use * symbol to denote Universal Selector

    II - Relationship with the elements (Combinators)
    - if there is relationship b/w the elements then we use combinators concept
     Catogires :-
      1.) child relationship (chid selector) :-
      - if there is a relationship of child(second element)
      with first element then use child relation concept
      - div element is supported
      - p is not supported for child relation
           Syntex : 
      div > h1{   
    color: brown;
    border: 7px solid green;
}

